# forecast
if (!require("forecast")) install.packages("forecast")

## Registered S3 method overwritten by 'quantmod':
##   method            from
##   as.zoo.data.frame zoo
library(forecast)

# AirPassengers
data("AirPassengers")

# 
plot(AirPassengers)

# ARIMA
fit <- auto.arima(AirPassengers)

# 
summary(fit)

## ARIMA(2,1,1)(0,1,0)[12] 
## 
## Coefficients:

##                      ACF1
## Training set -0.001248451
# 12
forecast <- forecast(fit, h = 12)

#

MSFT$SMA30 <- SMA(Cl(MSFT), 30)
GOOG$SMA30 <- SMA(Cl(GOOG), 30)

# 30
chartSeries(AAPL, name = "Apple Stock Price", TA = "addSMA(n = 30, col = 'red')")

#

#

2. ARAutoregressive Model

RAR

AR

AR

  • :
    • \(X_t = c + \phi_1 X_{t-1} + \phi_2 X_{t-2} + ... + \phi_p X_{t-p} + \epsilon_t\)
    • \(X_t\) \(\phi\) \(\epsilon_t\)

AR

R

RforecastAR

# 
getSymbols("AAPL", src = "yahoo", from = "2020-01-01", to = "2021-01-01")
## [1] "AAPL"
apple_stock <- Cl(AAPL)  #

AR

# AR
ar_model <- auto.arima(apple_stock, seasonal = FALSE)

# 
summary(ar_model)
## Series: apple_stock 
## ARIMA(2,1,2) 
## 
## Coefficients:
##           ar1      ar2     ma1     ma2
##       -1.8516  -0.9749  1.8266  0.9335
## s.e.   0.0384   0.0395  0.0656  0.0746
## 
## sigma^2 = 6.416:  log likelihood = -590.21
## AIC=1190.42   AICc=1190.67   BIC=1208.07
## 
## Training set error measures:
##                     ME     RMSE     MAE       MPE     MAPE      MASE       ACF1
## Training set 0.2307033 2.507812 1.80745 0.1885303 1.948679 0.9678808 -0.0980967

ARIMA

  • ARIMA(2,1,2) ARIMA
    • p= 2
    • d= 1
    • q= 2

  • ar1 (AR1) = -1.8516 = 0.0384
  • ar2 (AR2) = -0.9749 = 0.0395
  • ma1 (MA1) = 1.8266 = 0.0656
  • ma2 (MA2) = 0.9335 = 0.0746

ARMA

  • sigma^2 = 6.416
  • (log likelihood) = -590.210
  • AIC () = 1190.42
  • AICc = 1190.67AIC
  • BIC () = 1208.07AIC

  • ME () = 0.2307033
  • RMSE () = 2.507812
  • MAE () = 1.80745
  • MPE () = 0.1885303
  • MAPE () = 1.948679
  • MASE () = 0.9678808
  • ACF1 () = -0.09809670

ARIMA

# 10
forecast_ar <- forecast(ar_model, h = 10)

# 
plot(forecast_ar)

3. Autoregressive Moving Average, ARMA

ARMAARMA

  • :
    • \(X_t = c + \phi_1 X_{t-1} + ... + \phi_p X_{t-p} + \theta_1 \epsilon_{t-1} + ... + \theta_q \epsilon_{t-q} + \epsilon_t\)
  • :
    • ARMA
  • :
